{
  "stem": "7506.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES] My mother-- my grandmother asked my mother, my father, and of course, the two of us, to come with her to England.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my father refused to go to England with my grandmother, as he did not want to leave his parents and his brother and sister and their families.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My grandmother then asked my mother, would she please let us children, my sister and I, go with my grandmother to England.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my father said-- this is according to my mother-- my father said, where I go, my children go.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my grandmother [PAUSES] left about a week before September 1939, when war was declared by Britain against Germany because of the invasion of Poland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That was the last time-- although we didn't know it at the time-- that any of us saw my grandmother, my English grandmother.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She returned to England, and we stayed in Holland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my whole early life was spent on a boat between Holland and England.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother's brothers would visit us in Holland, or vice versa.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I've always been like between one country and another, because England was as much as my family as Holland was, although at that time, I didn't speak any English.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandmother could still speak a bit of Dutch.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my great grandmother, who we called-- we named Granny Cluck, because that was her-- that was her name, [PAUSES] she spoke Dutch with me, because that's all I could speak at that time.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, after the summer holidays, like is normal in Holland, we just went back to school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES] This was around the beginning of September 1939.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "School holidays would have been over, because they're summer holidays.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we would return to school normal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "To school.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not really.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
